Super John: <br><br>
Could have added tunnel rats and SAR to my posts above, but didn't want to overkill... you know how conservative I am!!!<br><br>
Probably everything we do, hear, and say is related to Vietnam either directly or indirectly.  We went to Vietnam with a set of preconcieved ideas...values... myths.. etc. stemming from our upbringings and accumulated lifes experiences.  Viet Nam did not make us killers or goodie two shoes... but it did impact severely upon all of us.  I often wonder if I would think differently now.. had I not been exposed to the war.<br><br>
I know that I have a low threshold for anger.  I realize that I have problems with trusting others, particularily politicians.  Control issues seem to dominate my insecure life for some reason.<br><br>
If my way of thinking hasn't been adversely affected... well, my ability to communicate has certainly been impacted upon.<br><br>
Perhaps, It would be wise for all of us to think about &quot;what&quot; we're thinking before we say what we &quot;think&quot; we're saying.<br><br>
You are a class act, John!  It matters not if you agree or disagree with me or anyone else, but we both have an appreciation for the fact that freedom to think precedes freedom of speech.<br><br>
This is not a History Course or Political Science 101, it is a site where Veterans and Non-veterans can say what they mean. Above all, it is a place where I can interact with other veterans as I search for answers.<br><br>
Cook Barela has my deepest respect!  But, then, I know him better than most here know him.  He may not say what pleases you... but he does say what is on his mind.  He may lack tact...but he is never lacking in truth.  Nor is he lacking in the other essential virtures of a truly good man.<br><br>
As an economicaly depressed Native American I am grossly familiar with racism and religious fanaticism.  But, in my 55 years, I have learned that the only thing that holds me back or moves me forward... is ME...not anyone else!<br><br>
You're a good man, John...you know what I mean!<br><br>
MTF<br><br>
 
